cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR. 

The paper deals with a dataset and task related to visual reasoning and natural language processing, which suggests that it could belong to several sub-categories. However, the focus on referring expression comprehension and the use of visual properties make it most likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) and Computational Linguistics (cs.CL) sub-categories. The use of reasoning logics and the evaluation of state-of-the-art models also suggest that it could belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Finally, the use of hard mining strategy and the potential for deeper analysis suggest that it could also belong to the Information Retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category.
